{"id":13321,"date":"2020-08-09T13:52:52","date_gmt":"2020-08-09T20:52:52","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=13321"},"modified":"2024-01-09T12:52:11","modified_gmt":"2024-01-09T20:52:11","slug":"fern-forest-trail","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/09\/fern-forest-trail\/","title":{"rendered":"FERN FOREST TRAIL"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"fusion-text\">\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>The Fern Forest Trail is a \u2018trail in the middle\u2019 which may be accessed from either the Balancing Rock Trail or the Summit Creek Trail. It is an \u2018out and back\u2019 trail unless you leave one vehicle at the Summit Creek parking area and another at the Balancing Rock Parking area.<\/em><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Location:<\/strong> West of Creston and the Creston Wildlife C<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> Easy A1<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation Gain:<\/strong> 180m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 1.4km one-way<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 2 hours<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> Spring to Fall<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong> Easy with good parking<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82F\/8<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive:<\/strong> Refer to Balancing Rock Trail and Summit Creek trail for driving instructions.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail:<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Option 1. Continue downhill from the actual Balancing Rock onto the \u2018skunk cabbage boardwalk\u2019 and turn right at the trail sign marked \u2018Fern Forest Trail\u2019.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">From the junction with Balancing Rock Trail, this is a shaded trail which continues downhill for 0.5 km through an amazing growth of skunk cabbage along a deteriorating boardwalk. During bug season, be prepared for lots of hungry \u2018followers\u2019. Continue under a power line to an old logging trail, cross the logging trail and hike approximately 1 km along a moderate ridge trail, then downhill to a \u201cFern Forest Trail\u201d registration box where the trail meets the Summit Creek Trail.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Option 2.\u00a0Follow Summit Creek Trail under the Highway 3 bridge for Summit Creek.\u00a0 The junction to Fern Forest Trail is a few hundred feet after this.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>What to Do:<\/strong> Connect with the other trails in the Creston Mountain system. Form loops or use shuttles.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>References:<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">https:\/\/www.crestonvalleytrails.ca\/trails\/fern-forest-trail\/<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Fern Forest Trail is a \u2018trail in the middle\u2019 which may be accessed from either the Balancing Rock Trail or the Summit Creek Trail. It is an \u2018out and back\u2019 trail unless you leave one vehicle at the Summit &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/09\/fern-forest-trail\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"aut